name: 𝚖𝚓ø𝚕𝚗𝚒𝚛
description:
𝚖𝚓ø𝚕𝚗𝚒𝚛 is based on the Mjølnir crater in Norway, on giant rock we call home. the art represents the latitudes and longitudes we've divided our planet up into, which turns into a blurry spin as time takes it's toll.

this is part of my 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐯𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬 collection. it combines my love for space & astronomy, with an abstract monochrome art style. every artwork is a satisfying infinite loop of motion.
